WEBVTT

00:17.430 --> 00:20.370
( <i>bell ringing</i> )

00:23.940 --> 00:25.440
( <i>whistle blowing</i> )

00:39.250 --> 00:43.630
( <i>playing the blues</i> )

00:59.140 --> 00:59.970
( <i>horn honking</i> )

01:04.340 --> 01:05.370
D-OHH!

01:05.440 --> 01:06.270
( <i>screams</i> )

01:27.050 --> 01:29.450
FORGOT THERE WAS
A PHYSICAL TODAY, HUH?

01:29.520 --> 01:30.720
YEAH.

01:30.790 --> 01:33.260
HEY, HOMER, CAN I BORROW
YOUR UNDERWEAR?

01:33.320 --> 01:34.390
NAH.

01:34.460 --> 01:36.030
THIS CAN'T BE RIGHT.

01:36.090 --> 01:38.000
THIS MAN HAS
104% BODY FAT.

01:38.060 --> 01:39.860
HEY, NO EATING
IN THE TANK.

01:39.930 --> 01:41.100
GO TO HELL.

01:41.160 --> 01:43.220
HOW WAS YOUR DAY AT WORK, DEAR?

01:43.300 --> 01:45.900
OH, THE USUAL--
STAND IN FRONT OF THIS.

01:45.970 --> 01:47.540
OPEN THAT.
PULL DOWN THIS.

01:47.600 --> 01:49.460
BEND OVER.
SPREAD APART THAT.

01:49.540 --> 01:51.610
TURN YOUR HEAD THAT WAY.
COUGH.

01:51.670 --> 01:52.870
Smithers:
<i>SIR, I'M AFRAID</i>

01:52.940 --> 01:54.410
HOMER SIMPSON IS STERILE.

01:54.480 --> 01:55.680
WHO?

01:55.740 --> 01:57.610
ONE OF YOUR CABBAGEHEADS
FROM SECTOR 7-G.

01:57.680 --> 01:59.480
TAKE A LOOK
AT THIS SPERM SAMPLE
FROM HIS RECENT PHYSICAL.

02:00.750 --> 02:03.390
( <i>snoring</i> )

02:03.450 --> 02:04.960
Burns:
EWW.

02:05.020 --> 02:09.230
Smithers:
NOW, COMPARE THIS
WITH A NORMAL SPERM SAMPLE.

02:09.290 --> 02:11.600
Burns:
OH, YES.

02:11.660 --> 02:14.600
I'M AFRAID RADIATION
FROM THE PLANT IS THE REASON
HE'S SHOOTING BLANKS.

02:14.660 --> 02:16.160
HE COULD SUE US
FOR MILLIONS.

02:16.230 --> 02:17.370
MOTHER OF PEARL.

02:17.430 --> 02:18.930
CALL MY LAWYERS!

02:19.000 --> 02:21.210
Burns:
BEFORE YOU BEGIN, LET ME
MAKE ONE THING CLEAR TO YOU.

02:21.270 --> 02:23.040
I WANT YOUR LEGAL ADVICE.

02:23.110 --> 02:24.340
I EVEN PAY FOR IT

02:24.410 --> 02:26.440
BUT TO ME, YOU'RE ALL VIPERS.

02:26.510 --> 02:29.180
YOU LIVE ON PERSONAL INJURY,
YOU LIVE ON DIVORCES.

02:29.240 --> 02:31.170
YOU LIVE ON PAIN AND MISERY!

02:31.250 --> 02:33.050
BUT I'M RAMBLING.

02:33.120 --> 02:34.550
ANYBODY WANT ANY COFFEE?

02:34.620 --> 02:35.790
I'LL HAVE SOME COFFEE.

02:35.850 --> 02:37.420
WANT IT BLACK,
DON'T YOU?

02:37.490 --> 02:38.920
BLACK LIKE YOUR HEART.

02:38.990 --> 02:40.360
IT'S SO HARD FOR ME
TO LISTEN TO YOU.

02:40.420 --> 02:42.420
I HATE YOU ALL SO MUCH!

02:42.490 --> 02:45.900
I'M SORRY. IT'S MY PROBLEM.
I'LL DEAL WITH IT.

02:45.960 --> 02:47.370
PLEASE CONTINUE.

02:47.430 --> 02:49.570
IF YOU OFFER MR. SIMPSON
A TOKEN SUM-- SAY A COUPLE THOU,

02:49.630 --> 02:50.900
HE'LL BE SO DAZZLED,

02:50.970 --> 02:54.010
HE'LL SIGN ANYTHING
YOU SHOVE UNDER HIS NOSE.

02:54.070 --> 02:55.610
OH, BRILLIANT--
A CASH SETTLEMENT.

02:55.670 --> 02:59.580
I COULD HAVE FIGURED THAT OUT,
YOU BUTTON-DOWN MAGGOT!

02:59.640 --> 03:00.750
YOU HAVE CREAM?

03:00.810 --> 03:02.410
OH, YES, OF COURSE.
WHERE ARE MY MANNERS?

03:04.780 --> 03:07.290
Man:
YEAH, I USED TO BE RICH.

03:07.350 --> 03:10.150
I OWNED MICKEY MOUSE
MASSAGE PARLORS.

03:10.220 --> 03:12.960
THEN THOSE DISNEY SLEAZEBALLS
SHUT ME DOWN.

03:13.020 --> 03:16.590
I SAID, "I'LL CHANGE THE LOGO--
PUT MICKEY'S PANTS BACK ON."

03:16.660 --> 03:18.930
SOME GUYS
YOU JUST CAN'T REASON WITH.

03:18.990 --> 03:21.620
I USED TO OWN
A SUCCESSFUL CAR COMPANY.

03:21.700 --> 03:24.640
MY STRATEGY WAS GIVING THEM
JAPANESE NAMES.

03:24.700 --> 03:27.110
YOU GUYS EVER DRIVE
A TEMPURA HATCHBACK?

03:27.170 --> 03:28.340
OH, YEAH.
SURE.

03:28.400 --> 03:30.030
I GOT HIT
BY ONE OF THOSE.

03:30.110 --> 03:32.310
YEAH, LIFE WAS SWEET.

03:32.370 --> 03:37.040
THEN I FOUND OUT
I HAD A LONG-LOST HALF BROTHER.

03:38.380 --> 03:39.320
HOMER?

03:39.380 --> 03:41.250
HERB?

03:41.320 --> 03:43.490
Herb:
<i>I LET HIM DESIGN A CAR
THAT WOULD</i>

03:43.550 --> 03:45.660
<i>MAKE OR BREAK MY COMPANY.</i>

03:45.720 --> 03:48.160
Announcer:
PRESENTING THE HOMER.

03:48.220 --> 03:49.980
( <i>crowd gasping</i> )

03:50.060 --> 03:50.960
( <i>gulping</i> )

03:53.100 --> 03:55.300
I'M RUINED!

03:55.360 --> 03:56.820
Herb:
FORBES <i> MAGAZINE CALLED IT:</i>

03:58.770 --> 04:00.340
LITTLE OVERBLOWN,
DON'T YOU THINK?

04:00.400 --> 04:01.630
WHAT ABOUT NEW COKE?

04:01.700 --> 04:03.770
HEY! I INVENTED THAT.

04:03.840 --> 04:06.440
YEAH, BUT ALL THAT'S
IN THE PAST

04:06.510 --> 04:09.910
BECAUSE THIS IS AMERICA,
AND IN AMERICA

04:09.980 --> 04:13.150
YOU'RE NEVER FINISHED
AS LONG AS YOU'VE GOT A BRAIN
IN YOUR HEAD

04:13.220 --> 04:16.320
BECAUSE ALL A MAN
REALLY NEEDS IS AN IDEA.

04:16.390 --> 04:18.090
WELL, I'M LICKED.
ME TOO.

04:18.150 --> 04:19.580
<i>NOW, THE NEXT EVENT</i>

04:19.660 --> 04:21.560
IN OUR LIVING ROOM OLYMPICS--

04:21.620 --> 04:23.150
THE ALWAYS CONTROVERSIAL
COUCH VAULT.

04:23.230 --> 04:25.160
I DO THIS
FOR STAINMASTER CARPETS

04:25.230 --> 04:27.570
PROUD SPONSOR
OF THE LIVING ROOM OLYMPICS.

04:33.970 --> 04:35.740
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TWO...?

04:35.800 --> 04:36.660
( <i>screaming</i> )

04:36.740 --> 04:37.840
OH, MY COUCH!

04:37.910 --> 04:39.840
THE ARMS, THE SEAT...

04:39.910 --> 04:41.610
THE DREAM IS OVER.

04:41.680 --> 04:43.110
ALL RIGHT, WHO DID THIS?

04:43.180 --> 04:44.920
WE WERE SITTING ON THE COUCH
QUIETLY CHATTING

04:44.980 --> 04:46.920
WHEN WE HEARD
A CREAKING NOISE.

04:46.980 --> 04:49.950
WE LEAPT OFF JUST IN TIME
TO SEE IT COLLAPSE.

04:50.020 --> 04:51.020
THERE, THERE

04:51.090 --> 04:53.060
YOU'RE SAFE NOW,
LITTLE SISTER.

04:53.120 --> 04:56.330
WHY DID THIS HAVE TO HAPPEN NOW
DURING PRIME TIME

04:56.390 --> 04:59.160
WHEN TV's BRIGHTEST STARS
COME OUT TO SHINE?

04:59.230 --> 05:01.900
OH, GOOD-BYE, OLD GIRL.

05:01.960 --> 05:04.760
WE'VE HAD
A LOT OF GREAT MEMORIES.

05:04.830 --> 05:07.100
Woman:
That's right.
I shot J.R.

05:07.170 --> 05:08.610
( <i>gasping</i> )

05:08.670 --> 05:11.910
Announcer:
Except for huge gaps
in the western states

05:11.970 --> 05:14.900
Hands Across America
was a complete success.

05:14.980 --> 05:20.120
All:
♪ HANDS ACROSS AMERICA... ♪

05:20.180 --> 05:22.690
Man:
Well, I never thought
I'd see it.

05:22.750 --> 05:25.220
They're dancing
on the Berlin Wall.

05:25.290 --> 05:28.430
These live and lively lovers
of liberation...

05:28.490 --> 05:29.960
BORING.

05:30.030 --> 05:33.230
Man #1:
Sorry I ruined your date,
Sergeant Carter.

05:33.300 --> 05:34.400
Man #2:
Pyle!

05:34.460 --> 05:35.890
( <i>chuckling</i> )

05:35.960 --> 05:40.160
WELL, FRIEND, YOU'RE GOING
BACK WHERE YOU CAME FROM

05:40.240 --> 05:42.370
THE CURB IN FRONT
OF FLANDERS'S HOUSE.

05:42.440 --> 05:44.010
NOW, LET'S SEE.

05:44.070 --> 05:45.500
I NEED AN IDEA.

05:45.570 --> 05:48.270
IDEA... IDEA!

05:48.340 --> 05:50.170
WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH ME?

05:50.250 --> 05:52.350
I USED TO HAVE
HUNDREDS OF IDEAS.

05:52.410 --> 05:53.340
( <i>baby crying</i> )

05:53.420 --> 05:54.920
Woman:
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

05:54.980 --> 05:56.640
I JUST CHANGED
YOUR DIAPER.

05:56.720 --> 05:57.990
ARE YOU HUNGRY?

05:58.050 --> 05:59.210
ARE YOU COLD?

05:59.290 --> 06:00.430
DO YOU WANT
TO GO HOME?

06:00.490 --> 06:02.630
LADY, YOU
JUST GAVE ME

06:02.690 --> 06:04.960
THE IDEA
OF A LIFETIME.

06:05.030 --> 06:06.930
- HOW DO I THANK YOU?
- PLEASE DON'T HURT ME.

06:07.000 --> 06:08.170
CONSIDER IT DONE.

06:08.230 --> 06:10.640
HEY, PAL, I HEARD
ABOUT THE COUCH.

06:10.700 --> 06:12.570
YEAH, YOU GOING
TO BE OKAY?

06:12.630 --> 06:16.060
YEAH. YOU KNOW, MY LIFE
JUST CAN'T GET ANY WORSE.

06:21.210 --> 06:22.550
THAT'S RIGHT.

06:22.610 --> 06:26.080
THERE'S NO WAY MY LIFE
COULD POSSIBLY GET ANY WORSE.

06:28.280 --> 06:30.680
Smithers:
Simpson, report to
Mr. Burns's office at once.

06:30.750 --> 06:31.850
D-OHH!

06:31.920 --> 06:34.490
IS THIS THE ONE
WITH THE LAZY SPERM?

06:34.560 --> 06:35.860
MM-HMM.

06:35.920 --> 06:38.920
AH, SIMPSON,
YOU BIG, VIRILE SON OF A GUN

06:38.990 --> 06:41.160
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
A CHECK FOR $2,000?

06:41.230 --> 06:42.170
WOULD I!

06:42.230 --> 06:43.530
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO

06:43.600 --> 06:45.040
IS SIGN THIS FORM.

06:45.100 --> 06:47.870
WAIT A MINUTE.
I'M NOT SIGNING ANYTHING
UNTIL I READ IT

06:47.940 --> 06:50.480
OR SOMEBODY GIVES ME
THE GIST OF IT.

06:50.540 --> 06:51.910
OOH. ALL RIGHT.

06:51.970 --> 06:54.600
WELL, IT JUST EXPLAINS
THAT YOU'VE...

06:54.680 --> 06:56.280
WON-- YES, THAT'S IT--

06:56.350 --> 06:59.220
WON THE FIRST ANNUAL...

06:59.280 --> 07:00.990
MONTGOMERY BURNS...

07:01.050 --> 07:04.360
UH... AWARD FOR...

07:04.420 --> 07:08.130
OUTSTANDING ACHIEVEMENT
IN THE FIELD OF...

07:08.190 --> 07:09.490
EXCELLENCE.

07:09.560 --> 07:11.960
DON'T I GET SOME KIND OF TROPHY?

07:12.030 --> 07:13.870
AND A BIG AWARD CEREMONY?

07:16.870 --> 07:20.670
Chorus:
♪ IT'S THE FIRST ANNUAL
MONTGOMERY BURNS ♪

07:20.740 --> 07:22.110
♪ AWARD FOR... ♪

07:24.170 --> 07:26.400
♪ OUTSTANDING ACHIEVEMENT
IN... ♪

07:28.540 --> 07:29.870
♪ THE FIELD OF ♪

07:29.950 --> 07:33.520
♪ EXCELLENCE! ♪

07:35.650 --> 07:37.720
YES. THAT WAS BONITA DeWOLF

07:37.790 --> 07:41.560
AND THE SPRINGFIELD
NUCLEAR PLANT SOFT-SHOE SOCIETY.

07:41.620 --> 07:43.850
THIS AWARD IS THE BIGGEST
FARCE I EVER SAW.

07:43.930 --> 07:45.300
WHAT ABOUT THE EMMYS?

07:45.360 --> 07:46.530
I STAND CORRECTED.

07:46.600 --> 07:48.830
AND NOW, TO PRESENT THE AWARD

07:48.900 --> 07:51.770
HERE'S FORMER
HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPION

07:51.830 --> 07:53.230
SMOKIN' JOE FRAZIER.

07:56.070 --> 07:59.010
WEBSTER'S DICTIONARY
DEFINES EXCELLENCE

07:59.070 --> 08:02.770
AS "THE QUALITY OR CONDITION
OF BEING EXCELLENT."

08:02.840 --> 08:04.310
AND NOW THE WINNER

08:04.380 --> 08:07.690
OF THE FIRST ANNUAL
MONTGOMERY BURNS AWARD

08:07.750 --> 08:11.360
FOR OUTSTANDING ACHIEVEMENT
IN THE FIELD OF EXCELLENCE.

08:11.420 --> 08:12.560
PLEASE, PLEASE...

08:12.620 --> 08:13.790
DAD, YOU KNOW YOU WON.

08:13.860 --> 08:14.830
DON'T JINX IT.

08:14.890 --> 08:17.830
THE WINNER: HOMER SIMPSON.

08:17.890 --> 08:19.750
OH, MY GOD!

08:19.830 --> 08:20.870
I WIN!

08:27.600 --> 08:28.700
( <i>screaming</i> )

08:28.770 --> 08:30.070
( <i>loud thump</i> )

08:32.410 --> 08:34.250
KEEP THOSE
PICKLED EGGS COMING.

08:34.310 --> 08:35.650
YOU CLEANED ME OUT.

08:35.710 --> 08:37.550
WHAT'S THE MATTER,
HOMER?

08:37.610 --> 08:38.570
CUMMERBUND TOO TIGHT?

08:38.650 --> 08:39.920
I MISS MY COUCH.

08:39.980 --> 08:41.450
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

08:41.520 --> 08:43.050
YOU LOST THE COUCH.

08:43.120 --> 08:45.320
I LOST
THE HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP.

08:45.390 --> 08:46.820
HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP.

08:46.890 --> 08:48.130
THERE'S LIKE THREE OF THOSE.

08:48.190 --> 08:50.160
THAT COUCH WAS ONE OF A KIND.

08:50.230 --> 08:51.930
I KNOW THINGS
ARE TOUGH NOW

08:51.990 --> 08:54.390
BUT ONE DAY,
YOU'LL BE WALKING ALONG

08:54.460 --> 08:56.160
AND YOU'LL SEE
A PIECE OF FURNITURE

08:56.230 --> 08:57.940
YOU CAN LOVE
JUST AS MUCH.

08:58.000 --> 08:59.400
HEY, FRAZIER,
SHUT UP!

08:59.470 --> 09:01.870
BARNEY, YOU BEEN RIDING
MY BACK ALL NIGHT.

09:01.940 --> 09:04.310
OH, YEAH?
CARE TO STEP OUTSIDE?

09:04.370 --> 09:05.730
LET'S DO IT.

09:08.440 --> 09:11.040
( <i>punching and screaming</i> )

09:11.110 --> 09:13.540
I THINK I'M GOING
TO TAKE A WALK.

09:13.620 --> 09:15.920
ALL RIGHT!
A PEANUT.

09:15.980 --> 09:17.910
( <i>crunching</i> )

09:17.990 --> 09:20.690
I'M TELLING YOU,
ALL A MAN NEEDS IS AN IDEA

09:20.760 --> 09:22.430
AND I'VE GOT AN IDEA.

09:22.490 --> 09:24.730
THEN HOW COME
YOU'RE STILL A BUM?

09:24.790 --> 09:26.890
ALL RIGHT.
A MAN NEEDS TWO THINGS--

09:26.960 --> 09:30.430
AN IDEA AND MONEY
TO GET IT OFF THE GROUND.

09:30.500 --> 09:32.700
HELLO, WHAT'S THIS?

09:32.770 --> 09:35.910
( <i>reading headline aloud</i> )

09:38.140 --> 09:39.940
HMM.

09:40.010 --> 09:41.710
ANY OF YOU GUYS KNOW

09:41.780 --> 09:43.710
WHICH FREIGHT
GOES TO SPRINGFIELD?

09:43.780 --> 09:45.020
( <i>train approaching</i> )

09:46.150 --> 09:47.750
UH-UH.

09:47.820 --> 09:49.420
NO.

09:49.480 --> 09:50.880
NO.

09:50.950 --> 09:52.580
THAT'S THE ONE!

09:56.160 --> 09:59.900
I FEEL SO EMPTY,
SO ALONE, SO COUCHLESS.

09:59.960 --> 10:01.830
( <i>gasping</i> )

10:01.900 --> 10:06.740
WOW! THE SPINEMELTER 2000.

10:06.800 --> 10:08.240
( <i>loud vibrating</i> )

10:08.300 --> 10:10.000
GIVE ME FULL POWER.

10:10.070 --> 10:11.040
- BUT, SIR...
- DAMN IT!

10:11.110 --> 10:12.980
I SAID FULL POWER.

10:14.210 --> 10:17.210
( <i>vibrations getting louder</i> )

10:17.280 --> 10:21.820
( <i>eerie, out-of-body music
playing</i> )

10:35.500 --> 10:36.830
Lisa:
<i>DAD?</i>

10:36.900 --> 10:37.770
DAD?

10:39.530 --> 10:42.030
( <i>voice quavering:</i> )
I'LL TAKE IT.

10:42.100 --> 10:44.730
THIS CHAIR IS $2,000.

10:44.810 --> 10:47.750
WE CAN BUY A WHOLE
LIVING ROOM SET FOR THAT.

10:47.810 --> 10:50.050
THERE'S AN EMPTY SPOT
I'VE ALWAYS HAD INSIDE ME.

10:50.110 --> 10:52.420
I TRIED TO FILL IT
WITH FAMILY, RELIGION

10:52.480 --> 10:55.090
COMMUNITY SERVICE,
BUT THOSE WERE DEAD ENDS.

10:55.150 --> 10:57.350
I THINK THIS CHAIR
IS THE ANSWER.

10:57.420 --> 10:59.320
THIS MONEY WAS A BLESSING.
WE CAN'T JUST SPEND IT

10:59.390 --> 11:01.390
ON SOME
CREATURE COMFORT.

11:01.460 --> 11:03.930
ALL RIGHT,
WE WON'T GET THE CHAIR.

11:03.990 --> 11:06.430
NOW EXCUSE ME
WHILE I KISS THE SKY.

11:06.490 --> 11:09.690
( <i>loud vibrating</i> )

11:12.230 --> 11:13.960
HMM...

11:17.140 --> 11:20.580
( <i>chimes ringing melodically)</i>

11:20.640 --> 11:22.110
YES?

11:22.180 --> 11:24.450
OH, SORRY,
I MUST HAVE THE WRONG HOUSE.

11:24.510 --> 11:26.710
THAT'S WHERE
YOU'RE WRONG, FRIEND.

11:26.780 --> 11:28.320
AREN'T WE IN LUCK?
TODAY'S OUR TITHE DAY

11:28.380 --> 11:30.540
AND WE'VE GOT OURSELVES
A TRANSIENT.

11:30.620 --> 11:31.560
COME IN, MY FRIEND.

11:31.620 --> 11:34.090
LET US FEED AND BATHE YOU.

11:34.160 --> 11:36.730
HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.
DAD, CAN I ANOINT
THE SORES ON HIS FEET?

11:36.790 --> 11:38.960
I THINK
IT'S MOM'S TURN, SON.

11:39.030 --> 11:40.600
OH, NO FAIR.

11:40.660 --> 11:41.970
THANKS FOR THE SUIT.

11:42.030 --> 11:44.140
WELL, IF YOU EVER WANT
TO SPEND THE NIGHT

11:44.200 --> 11:46.900
MAUDE AND I
CAN SLEEP ON CARD TABLES.

11:46.970 --> 11:49.610
♪ ONWARD, CHRISTIAN SOLDIERS ♪

11:49.670 --> 11:52.740
( <i>all:</i> )
♪ MARCHING AS TO WAR... ♪

11:52.810 --> 11:54.450
THEY'RE SINGING AGAIN.

11:54.510 --> 11:55.950
LOUSY NEIGHBORS.

11:56.010 --> 11:57.550
WISH I WAS DEAF.

11:57.610 --> 11:59.440
( <i>doorbell ringing</i> )

11:59.510 --> 12:01.380
WHAT AM I GOING TO SAY?

12:01.450 --> 12:03.690
THIS IS THE GUY WHO RUINED ME.

12:03.750 --> 12:06.220
BUT ON THE OTHER HAND,
HE'S FAMILY.

12:06.290 --> 12:09.090
SO MANY CONFLICTING EMOTIONS,
HOW TO EXPRESS THEM.

12:10.430 --> 12:11.300
HERB?

12:15.600 --> 12:17.330
( <i>both:</i> )
UNCKY HERB!

12:17.400 --> 12:18.670
BART! LISA!

12:18.730 --> 12:20.490
I'M SO GLAD TO SEE YOU.

12:20.570 --> 12:22.670
YOU WEREN'T SO GLAD TO SEE ME.

12:22.740 --> 12:25.080
I'M SORRY,
BUT I'M STILL MAD AT YOU.

12:25.140 --> 12:28.480
EVERY WORD YOU SAY JUST MAKES ME
WANT TO PUNCH YOU IN THE FACE.

12:28.540 --> 12:31.470
WELL, WHILE YOU'RE A GUEST
IN MY HOME, COULD YOU JUST
KICK ME IN THE BUTT?

12:31.550 --> 12:34.390
I'LL TRY, BUT I'M NOT
MAKING ANY PROMISES.

12:34.450 --> 12:36.420
HERB!
HOW HAVE YOU BEEN?

12:36.480 --> 12:38.710
I'VE BEEN LIVING
IN A CARDBOARD BOX

12:38.790 --> 12:41.760
SLEEPING ON GRATES,
EATING OUT OF DUMPSTERS. YOU?

12:41.820 --> 12:43.250
CAN'T COMPLAIN.

12:43.330 --> 12:45.130
LET ME GIVE YOU
THE GRAND TOUR.

12:45.190 --> 12:47.690
THIS IS ONE
OF OUR MANY LIGHT SWITCHES.

12:47.760 --> 12:50.320
IT FUNCTIONS
IN BOTH THE ON AND OFF MODE.

12:50.400 --> 12:52.270
ON, OFF. ON, OFF.

12:52.330 --> 12:54.430
HE KNOWS HOW TO WORK
A LIGHT SWITCH.

12:54.500 --> 12:55.760
OH, YEAH, RIGHT.

12:55.840 --> 12:57.470
WHAT'S THIS SWITCH FOR?

12:57.540 --> 13:00.340
( <i>playing "Deck the Halls"</i> )

13:00.410 --> 13:02.080
THIS IS REALLY GOOD,
MARGE.

13:02.140 --> 13:05.110
I GOT THE RECIPE FROM
THE UTILITY GRADE BEEF COUNCIL.

13:05.180 --> 13:06.780
THEY DO GOOD WORK.

13:06.850 --> 13:09.820
UNCKY HERB, WHAT ADVICE
WOULD YOU GIVE TO A BOY

13:09.880 --> 13:12.810
WHO WILL MOST LIKELY BECOME
A BUM LIKE YOURSELF?

13:12.890 --> 13:14.590
DISCARDED PIZZA BOXES

13:14.660 --> 13:16.930
ARE AN INEXPENSIVE SOURCE
OF CHEESE.

13:16.990 --> 13:19.360
LISA, AREN'T YOU HAPPY
TO SEE ME?

13:19.430 --> 13:21.300
WHY DIDN'T YOU WRITE?

13:21.360 --> 13:22.690
HEY, IF I WROTE TO YOU
WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO SAY?

13:22.760 --> 13:24.390
"DEAR LISA, LAST NIGHT

13:24.470 --> 13:27.040
I USED A RAT FOR A PILLOW
THANKS TO YOUR POP"?

13:27.100 --> 13:28.740
I SEE YOUR POINT.

13:28.800 --> 13:32.300
♪ WHETHER YOU'RE DRIVING
NEAR OR FAR ♪

13:32.370 --> 13:35.740
♪ POWELL MAKES
A POW-POW-POWERFUL CAR. ♪

13:35.810 --> 13:39.880
MAGGIE, I'M GOING TO LET YOU IN
ON A LITTLE SECRET.

13:39.950 --> 13:42.990
YOU'RE GOING
TO MAKE ME RICH AGAIN.

13:43.050 --> 13:44.990
YES, YOU ARE.

13:45.050 --> 13:46.850
YES, YOU ARE.

13:46.920 --> 13:49.230
ONE, TWO, THREE...
VENTNOR AVENUE.

13:49.290 --> 13:51.030
AND WHILE ON
VENTNOR AVENUE

13:51.090 --> 13:53.890
YOU'LL BE STAYING
AT THE FABULOUS HOTEL LISA.

13:53.960 --> 13:55.930
A VALET
WILL BE AROUND SHORTLY

13:56.000 --> 13:57.670
TO PARK
YOUR THIMBLE.

13:57.730 --> 14:00.260
OF COURSE, THERE IS
THE UNPLEASANT MATTER
OF THE BILL.

14:00.340 --> 14:01.610
GET TO THE POINT.

14:01.670 --> 14:03.270
1150 BONES.

14:03.340 --> 14:04.710
( <i>groaning</i> )

14:04.770 --> 14:06.270
THAT'S ALL I GOT.

14:06.340 --> 14:08.150
BROKE AGAIN, EH, HERB?

14:08.210 --> 14:10.180
JUST LIKE IN REAL LIFE.

14:10.250 --> 14:13.720
I GUESS YOU'RE JUST NOT
MUCH OF A BUSINESSMAN.

14:13.780 --> 14:15.420
MAYBE WE SHOULD PLAY
ANOTHER GAME.

14:15.480 --> 14:18.180
WHY ARE WE PLAYING GAMES
WHEN WE GOT TWO GRAND
IN THE BANK?

14:18.250 --> 14:20.950
REMEMBER WHEN DAD WON THE FIRST
ANNUAL MONTGOMERY BURNS AWARD.

14:21.020 --> 14:23.380
FOR OUTSTANDING ACHIEVEMENT
IN THE FIELD OF EXCELLENCE?

14:23.460 --> 14:24.900
WELL, I THINK
WE SHOULD INVEST

14:24.960 --> 14:27.430
IN A SET OF THE "GREAT BOOKS
OF WESTERN CIVILIZATION."

14:27.500 --> 14:30.030
LOOK AT THIS AD
FROM <i>NEW REPUBLIC FOR KIDS.</i>

14:30.100 --> 14:32.970
"EACH MONTH, A NEW CLASSIC
WILL BE DELIVERED TO OUR DOOR."

14:33.030 --> 14:35.400
<i>"PARADISE REGAINED,
MARTIN CHUZZLEWIT</i>

14:35.470 --> 14:38.780
OR HERMAN MELVILLE'S
TWIN CLASSICS, <i>OMOOANDTYPEE."</i>

14:38.840 --> 14:41.650
WAIT, MARGE, DIDN'T YOU
WANT TO SPEND THAT MONEY
ON A VIBRATING CHAIR?

14:41.710 --> 14:43.410
THAT WAS YOUR IDEA.

14:43.480 --> 14:45.250
I THINK WE SHOULD
GET A MACHINE GUN.

14:45.310 --> 14:47.270
WE COULD USE IT TO HUNT GAME,
SPELL OUT THINGS

14:47.350 --> 14:48.920
OR RING IN THE NEW YEAR.

14:48.980 --> 14:52.310
WELL, I REALLY THINK WE NEED
TO REPLACE THE WASHER AND DRYER.

14:52.390 --> 14:53.490
( <i>loud rumbling</i> )

14:53.560 --> 14:55.930
( <i>screeching meow</i> )

14:55.990 --> 14:58.300
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO SPEND $2,000

14:58.360 --> 15:00.860
TO GIVE A BROKEN MAN
A SECOND CHANCE?

15:00.930 --> 15:02.170
NAH.

15:02.230 --> 15:03.970
WAIT, HERB,
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

15:04.030 --> 15:05.400
BUH, BUH, BUH, BUH--
NOT HERE.

15:05.470 --> 15:07.070
COME INTO
THE DINING ROOM.

15:07.140 --> 15:09.010
I WANNA GIVE YOU
A 20-MINUTE PRESENTATION

15:09.070 --> 15:10.670
THAT WILL CHANGE
THE WORLD.

15:10.740 --> 15:13.240
20 MINUTES? OH...

15:13.310 --> 15:15.980
OKAY, NOW BEFORE I TELL YOU
ABOUT MY IDEA

15:16.040 --> 15:18.040
I'D LIKE TO SHOW YOU THIS.

15:23.120 --> 15:25.990
IT'S DRINKING THE WATER!

15:26.050 --> 15:27.410
TAKE IT EASY, HOMER.

15:27.490 --> 15:28.860
THIS IS AN EXAMPLE

15:28.920 --> 15:31.820
OF HOW ONE LITTLE IDEA,
CAREFULLY MARKETED...

15:31.890 --> 15:34.360
THIS IS THE GREATEST INVENTION
IN THE WORLD.

15:34.430 --> 15:36.600
YOU'LL MAKE A MILLION DOLLARS.

15:36.660 --> 15:38.930
NO, HOMER, THAT INVENTION
IS OUT ALREADY.

15:39.000 --> 15:41.270
I'M JUST USING IT AS AN EXAMPLE.

15:41.340 --> 15:44.310
IT'S GOING BACK FOR MORE.

15:44.370 --> 15:46.270
OH...

15:46.340 --> 15:48.450
HOMER, <i>THIS</i> IS MY INVENTION.

15:48.510 --> 15:50.810
NOW OF COURSE,
WITH THESE BLUEPRINTS

15:50.880 --> 15:52.420
YOU'LL HAVE TO USE
YOUR IMAGINATION.

15:52.480 --> 15:55.420
Homer:
HMM? WHAT THE--?

15:56.890 --> 16:00.460
HMM...

16:00.520 --> 16:02.160
( <i>laughing</i> )

16:02.220 --> 16:03.820
IT'S A BABY TRANSLATOR.

16:03.890 --> 16:05.460
IT MEASURES THE PITCH

16:05.530 --> 16:08.770
THE FREQUENCY, AND THE URGENCY
OF A BABY'S CRIES.

16:08.830 --> 16:11.600
THEN IT TELLS WHOEVER'S AROUND
IN PLAIN ENGLISH

16:11.670 --> 16:14.000
EXACTLY WHAT THE BABY
IS TRYING TO SAY.

16:14.070 --> 16:16.110
EVERYTHING FROM "CHANGE ME"

16:16.170 --> 16:18.410
TO "TURN OFF
THAT DAMN RAFFI RECORD."

16:18.470 --> 16:20.400
THAT'S A VERY
CLEVER IDEA.

16:20.480 --> 16:23.110
ALL I NEED IS
A COUPLE OF THOUSAND DOLLARS

16:23.180 --> 16:24.750
TO BUILD A PROTOTYPE.

16:24.810 --> 16:26.470
YOU'LL HAVE
YOUR MONEY BACK

16:26.550 --> 16:27.990
IN 30 DAYS, I SWEAR.

16:28.050 --> 16:30.020
I THINK WE OWE A DEBT
TO UNCKY HERB.

16:30.080 --> 16:32.280
HE TOOK US IN TO HIS HOME
AND DAD DESTROYED HIM.

16:32.350 --> 16:34.920
DAD, YOU KNOW SOME SHYSTER
WILL BILK YOU OUT OF YOUR MONEY.

16:34.990 --> 16:36.990
IT MAY AS WELL
BE YOUR BROTHER.

16:37.060 --> 16:39.060
ALL RIGHT, HERB,
I'LL LEND YOU THE 2,000 BUCKS

16:39.130 --> 16:42.900
BUT YOU HAVE TO FORGIVE ME
AND TREAT ME LIKE A BROTHER.

16:42.960 --> 16:45.260
- NO.
- OKAY, THEN GIVE ME
THE DRINKING BIRD.

16:46.970 --> 16:48.540
( <i>Maggie trying to talk</i> )

16:48.600 --> 16:50.200
LET'S SEE,
WHAT COULD YOU BE
TRYING TO SAY?

16:50.270 --> 16:52.640
( <i>baby talk</i> )
NOTHING DOWNSTAIRS.

16:52.710 --> 16:54.480
YOU JUST
TOOK A NAP.

16:54.540 --> 16:55.640
( <i>sucking</i> )

16:55.710 --> 16:57.920
"I WANT TO SUCK
YOUR NOSE."

16:57.980 --> 17:00.450
HOOGA-BOOGA, HOOGA-BOOGA.

17:00.520 --> 17:01.490
( <i>baby talk</i> )

17:01.550 --> 17:03.950
"I'M SCARED."

17:04.020 --> 17:05.090
HMM...

17:05.150 --> 17:06.980
THE AMPLITUDE
OF THE SIGN WAVE

17:07.060 --> 17:08.860
IS INSUFFICIENT
FOR "BURP ME"

17:08.920 --> 17:11.090
AND THIS SAWTOOTH FORMATION
IS SOMETHING I'VE NEV--

17:11.160 --> 17:12.100
BLAH!

17:12.160 --> 17:13.760
EUREKA.

17:13.830 --> 17:15.770
NOW, I BET
YOU'RE ALL WONDERING

17:15.830 --> 17:17.400
WHAT LIES UNDER
THIS SHEET.

17:17.470 --> 17:20.040
NOT REALLY. WE PEEKED INSIDE
WHILE YOU WERE IN THE JOHN.

17:20.100 --> 17:21.210
OH.

17:21.270 --> 17:23.040
WELL, HERE IT IS AGAIN...

17:23.100 --> 17:25.370
MY BABY TRANSLATOR.

17:25.440 --> 17:29.410
OOH!

17:29.480 --> 17:30.850
MARGE,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO HUMOR ME.

17:30.910 --> 17:32.120
WELL, IT'S
PRETTY INGRAINED.

17:32.180 --> 17:33.620
WHAT DO YOU THINK,
HOMER?

17:33.680 --> 17:36.290
THIS IS THE STUPIDEST
THING I'VE EVER SEEN.

17:36.350 --> 17:39.190
I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE BLEW 2,000 BUCKS ON IT

17:39.250 --> 17:40.610
WHEN RIGHT NOW

17:40.690 --> 17:42.760
ROLLERS COULD BE KNEADING
MY BUTTOCKS.

17:42.820 --> 17:44.720
COULD YOU STOP THINKING
ABOUT YOUR ASS?

17:44.790 --> 17:47.120
I TRY,
BUT I CAN'T.

17:47.200 --> 17:48.500
( <i>baby talk</i> )

17:48.560 --> 17:49.860
Lavish attention on me

17:49.930 --> 17:51.100
and entertain me.

17:51.170 --> 17:53.000
OH, MAGGIE,
YOU TALKED!

17:53.070 --> 17:54.340
YOU SEE?

17:54.400 --> 17:57.070
IT TELLS YOU EXACTLY
WHAT'S ON THE BABY'S MIND.

17:57.140 --> 17:58.080
MAGGIE.

17:58.140 --> 17:59.140
MAGGIE.

17:59.210 --> 18:00.240
( <i>baby talk</i> )

18:00.310 --> 18:01.250
Where did you go?

18:01.310 --> 18:02.480
PEEK-A-BOO!

18:02.540 --> 18:03.400
( <i>baby talk</i> )

18:03.480 --> 18:04.750
Oh, there you are.

18:04.810 --> 18:05.870
Very amusing.

18:05.950 --> 18:07.750
HOMER,
NOW WHAT DO YOU THINK?

18:07.820 --> 18:08.850
I DON'T KNOW, HERB.

18:08.920 --> 18:11.050
PEOPLE ARE AFRAID
OF NEW THINGS.

18:11.120 --> 18:13.160
YOU SHOULD HAVE TAKEN
AN EXISTING PRODUCT

18:13.220 --> 18:14.530
AND PUT A CLOCK IN IT
OR SOMETHING.

18:14.590 --> 18:16.560
HOMER, EVERY MOTHER
IN THE COUNTRY

18:16.620 --> 18:18.090
IS GOING TO
WANT ONE OF THESE.

18:18.160 --> 18:19.800
( <i>baby talk</i> )

18:19.860 --> 18:21.470
I have soiled myself.

18:21.530 --> 18:22.630
How embarrassing.

18:24.600 --> 18:26.270
I GAVE HERB ALL THE MONEY
I HAD IN THE WORLD.

18:26.330 --> 18:30.730
AND HE STILL TREATS ME LIKE
SOMETHING HE DUG OUT OF HIS EAR.

18:30.810 --> 18:33.140
DON'T WORRY, HE CAN'T STAY
MAD AT YOU FOREVER.

18:33.210 --> 18:34.510
HE <i>IS</i> YOUR BROTHER.

18:34.580 --> 18:36.750
BUT WHEN IS HE GOING
TO ACT LIKE IT?

18:39.380 --> 18:41.120
( <i>crowd murmuring</i> )

18:46.520 --> 18:47.720
( <i>plane buzzing</i> )

18:47.790 --> 18:49.260
THIS RADIO-CONTROLLED PLANE

18:49.320 --> 18:51.520
GIVES YOUR BABY
THE CHANCE TO FLY

18:51.590 --> 18:53.120
JUST LIKE MY SON HERE.

18:53.190 --> 18:57.820
HE CAN EXECUTE THE BARREL ROLL,
THE LOOP-THE-LOOP

18:57.900 --> 19:00.470
AND BRING IT IN
FOR THE PERFECT LANDING.

19:00.540 --> 19:01.410
( <i>crowd gasping</i> )

19:01.470 --> 19:02.410
OH, DEAR.

19:02.470 --> 19:04.510
MY WIFE IS GOING TO KILL ME.

19:07.180 --> 19:09.050
( <i>baby talk</i> )

19:09.110 --> 19:10.980
I only want to eat candy.

19:11.050 --> 19:12.620
THEN THAT'S ALL YOU'LL GET.

19:12.680 --> 19:14.550
( <i>baby talk</i> )

19:14.620 --> 19:16.620
This leash demeans us both.

19:16.680 --> 19:18.080
- I'LL TAKE TWO!
- I'LL TAKE A DOZEN!

19:18.150 --> 19:19.210
I REPRESENT

19:19.290 --> 19:20.920
THE PRECIOUS BABY
DISCOUNT STORES.

19:20.990 --> 19:22.030
I'LL TAKE 50,000!

19:22.090 --> 19:23.760
I'M RICH AGAIN!

19:23.830 --> 19:24.760
U.S.A.!

19:24.830 --> 19:26.100
U.S.A.!

19:26.160 --> 19:27.530
U.S.A.!

19:27.600 --> 19:28.900
<i>HOMER,</i>

19:28.960 --> 19:31.230
HERE'S A CHECK
FOR $2,000.

19:31.300 --> 19:33.670
I ALSO WANTED TO GIVE YOU
EACH A LITTLE SOMETHING

19:33.740 --> 19:35.110
FOR BELIEVING IN ME.

19:35.170 --> 19:37.170
LISA, THIS IS
THE FIRST VOLUME

19:37.240 --> 19:39.510
OF "THE GREAT BOOKS
OF WESTERN CIVILIZATION."

19:39.570 --> 19:41.770
YOU'LL RECEIVE A NEW ONE
EVERY MONTH

19:41.840 --> 19:43.870
FROM <i>BEOWULF
</i>TO <i>LESS THAN ZERO.</i>

19:43.950 --> 19:47.120
FINALLY A COPY OF <i>ETHAN FROME
</i>TO CALL MY OWN.

19:47.180 --> 19:49.090
NOW BART, I KNOW YOU'RE
TOO YOUNG

19:49.150 --> 19:50.420
FOR THAT MACHINE GUN
YOU WANTED,

19:50.490 --> 19:51.920
BUT I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
SOMETHING

19:51.990 --> 19:53.960
THAT WILL MAKE SURE
WHEN YOU'RE OLD ENOUGH

19:54.020 --> 19:55.860
YOU CAN STILL BUY ONE...

19:55.920 --> 19:58.450
A MEMBERSHIP IN THE NATIONAL
RIFLE ASSOCIATION.

19:58.530 --> 19:59.960
WOW! THE N.R.A.!

20:00.030 --> 20:03.130
CAN I GET ARMOR-PIERCING,
CYANIDE-TIPPED BULLETS TOO?

20:03.200 --> 20:04.800
IT'S IN THE CONSTITUTION, SON.

20:04.870 --> 20:06.270
MAGGIE

20:06.330 --> 20:07.690
WHO BROUGHT ME
MY FORTUNE

20:07.770 --> 20:09.110
I'LL GIVE YOU

20:09.170 --> 20:11.110
ANYTHING YOU WANT
IN THIS WORLD.

20:11.170 --> 20:12.480
( <i>baby talk</i> )

20:12.540 --> 20:14.780
I want what the dog's eating.

20:14.840 --> 20:16.570
- D-OHH!
- I'LL GET YOU
SOMETHING NICE.

20:16.640 --> 20:19.470
NOW, MARGE...
HERB, I APPRECIATE
YOUR GENEROSITY,

20:19.550 --> 20:20.750
BUT I DON'T NEED
ANY GIFT FROM YOU.

20:20.820 --> 20:22.320
YOU'RE TOO LATE, MARGE.

20:22.380 --> 20:24.480
I GOT YOU
A NEW WASHER AND DRYER

20:24.550 --> 20:27.020
AND I SOLD THE OLD ONES
FOR 50 BUCKS.

20:27.090 --> 20:28.930
( <i>shouting and cheering</i> )
GO, GO GO!

20:28.990 --> 20:31.060
( <i>loud rumbling</i> )
COME ON, WASHER!

20:31.130 --> 20:32.230
( <i>cheering</i> )

20:32.290 --> 20:35.160
OH, YOU STUPID DRYER!

20:35.230 --> 20:36.500
HERB, I DON'T THINK

20:36.560 --> 20:39.560
THERE'S A VIBRATING CHAIR
IN THAT BAG FOR ME.

20:39.630 --> 20:41.700
HOMER,
WALK ME TO MY CAR.

20:42.970 --> 20:44.170
WHAT DO I GET?
WHAT DO I GET?

20:44.240 --> 20:46.110
IT'S NOT ANOTHER
PUNCH IN THE FACE, IS IT?

20:46.170 --> 20:47.500
BECAUSE IF IT IS,
I DON'T WANT IT.

20:47.580 --> 20:49.450
THIS IS WHAT YOU GET,
HOMER.

20:49.510 --> 20:50.810
I FORGIVE YOU.

20:50.880 --> 20:53.550
YOU CAN CALL ME BROTHER,
AND I CAN DO THE SAME.

20:53.610 --> 20:54.540
THAT'S IT?

20:54.620 --> 20:55.850
THAT'S IT.

20:55.920 --> 20:58.690
I SEE YOUR POINT...
BROTHER.

20:58.750 --> 21:00.580
GIVE ME A HUG...
BROTHER.

21:00.660 --> 21:01.860
ALL RIGHT

21:01.920 --> 21:04.720
BUT I NEVER REALLY
HUGGED A MAN BEFORE.

21:06.930 --> 21:09.530
( <i>both chuckling</i> )

21:09.600 --> 21:11.540
HOMER, I BOUGHT YOU
THE DAMN CHAIR.

21:11.600 --> 21:13.470
( <i>loud smacking</i> )

21:13.530 --> 21:14.860
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON.

21:14.940 --> 21:16.210
GO ON,
THAT'S ENOUGH.

21:16.270 --> 21:17.370
ALL RIGHT,
GET OUT OF HERE.

21:25.680 --> 21:28.320
Captioned by
The Caption Center
WGBH Educational Foundation

22:33.210 --> 22:34.070
SHH!
